{"lemma":"سَمْعُ","slug":"سَمْعُ","root":"س.م.ع","root_slug":"س-م-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/س-م-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَمْع","root":"سمع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":22},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20715","n20716","n20730"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hear","examples":[{"text":"لَنْ تَسْمَعَ شَيْئًا","english":"You won't hear anything."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hear of, to hear about","examples":[{"text":"فَلَمَّا سَمِعَتْ بِمَكْرِهِنَّ أَرْسَلَتْ إِلَيْهِنَّ وَأَعْتَدَتْ لَهُنَّ مُتَّكَأً وَآتَتْ كُلَّ وَاحِدَةٍ مِّنْهُنَّ سِكِّينًا وَقَالَتِ اخْرُجْ عَلَيْهِنَّ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hear from"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to learn, to be told"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to listen to, to pay attention to, to hear someone out"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to learn by hearsay"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to overhear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lend an ear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make hear, to let hear, to give someone something to hear","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to recite"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dishonor, to discredit"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَمِعَ (samiʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hearing, sense of hearing","examples":[{"text":"خَتَمَ ٱللَّهُ عَلَىٰ قُلُوبِهِمْ وَعَلَىٰ سَمْعِهِمْ وَعَلَىٰٓ أَبْصَـٰرِهِمْ غِشَـٰوَةٌ وَلَهُمْ عَذَابٌ عَظِيمٌ","english":"Allah has sealed their hearts and their hearing, and their sight is covered. They will suffer a tremendous punishment."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"audition"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ear"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-Semitic *šamaʕ-. Cognate with Hebrew שמע."},"ipa":["/sa.mi.ʕa/","/sam.ma.ʕa/","/samʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20715","headword_ar":"سَمْعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEa","text_ar":"سَمِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) like ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAEN","text_ar":"سَمَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [&c.,] or the latter is a simple subst. [used in the abstract sense of the former]. (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEFA waTaAEapF","text_ar":"سَمْعًا وَطَاعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomaEu samoEFA waA^uTiyEu TaAEapF","text_ar":"اَسْمَعُ سَمْعًا وَاُطِيعُ طَاعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", an emphatic mode of expression, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I hear and I obey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEotu samoEFA waA^aTaEotu TaAEapF","text_ar":"سَمِعْتُ سَمْعًا وَاَطَعْتُ طَاعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means the same, but more emphatically;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAEapF","text_ar":"طَاعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"being a quasi-inf. n. for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iTaAEapF","text_ar":"اـِطَاعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":";] the verb [of each] being understood: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN waTaAEapN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ وَطَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoriY *`lika","text_ar":"اَمْرِى ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoriY samoEN waTaAEapN","text_ar":"اَمْرِى سَمْعٌ وَطَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My affair is hearing and obeying"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) You say also, [in like manner,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a samoEFA laA balogFA","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ سَمْعًا لَا بَلْغًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN laA","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balogN","text_ar":"بَلْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoEN","text_ar":"سِمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEu A^u*uniY fulaAnFA yaquwla","text_ar":"سَمْعُ اُذُنِى فُلَانًا يَقُولَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [said to be] the only instance of the kind among inf. ns. of trans. verbs except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oYu","text_ar":"رَاْىُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayoniY","text_ar":"عَيْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rA^Y","text_ar":"راى"},{"kind":"text","text":",) [in a copy of the M, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rA^Y","text_ar":"راى"},{"kind":"text","text":", written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEa A*nY","text_ar":"سَمْعَ اذنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oYa EynY","text_ar":"رَاْىَ عينى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*nY","text_ar":"اذنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoEu","text_ar":"سِمْعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*nY","text_ar":"اذنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEapu","text_ar":"سَمْعَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*nY","text_ar":"اذنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoEapu","text_ar":"سِمْعَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My ear heard"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my ear's hearing"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one say that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K) ―         -b2-  [As a simple subst., it signifies] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sense of the ear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) [i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hearing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faculty in the ear whereby it perceives sounds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Thus in the Kur [1. 36],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo A^aloqaY","text_ar":"اَوْ اَلْقَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amoEu","text_ar":"السَّمْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Or who hearkeneth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel.) [And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Als~amoEi","text_ar":"اُمُّ السَّمْعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The brain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Als~amiyEi","text_ar":"اُمُّ السَّمِيعِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Darabahu EalaY A^um~i Als~amoEi","text_ar":"ضَرَبَهُ عَلَى اُمِّ السَّمْعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck him upon the brain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  [It is also used for the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomaEa","text_ar":"اَسْمَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Hence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAluwA *`lika samoEa A^u*uniY","text_ar":"قَالُوا ذٰلِكَ سَمْعَ اُذُنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*nY","text_ar":"اذنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoEa","text_ar":"سِمْعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*nY","text_ar":"اذنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAEa","text_ar":"سَمَاعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*nY","text_ar":"اذنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAEapa","text_ar":"سَمَاعَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isomaAEahaA","text_ar":"اـِسْمَاعَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They said that making my ear to hear"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) and one may say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEFA","text_ar":"سَمْعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making to hear"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: this latter one says when he does not particularize himself. (Sb, K.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~amahu simoEahumo","text_ar":"كَلَّمَهُ سِمْعَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, meaning, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spoke to him making them to hear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that they heard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A@ll~`hi waAlEulamaA='i A^an~iY ↓ \n      samaAEa\n                      \n                     \n                        A^aEuw*u bixayori xaAlika yaAA@bona Eamoriw"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Making God and the learned men to hear that I seek protection by the goodness of thy maternal uncle, O son of 'Amr;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEuw*u biHaqowi xaAlika","text_ar":"اَعُوذُ بِحَقْوِ خَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have recourse for protection to thy maternal uncle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus in the TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hqw","text_ar":"حقو"},{"kind":"text","text":";] using the subst. in the place of the inf. n., as though he said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isomaAEFA","text_ar":"اـِسْمَاعًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~iY","text_ar":"عَنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*otu *`lika Eanohu samoEFA","text_ar":"اَخَذْتُ ذٰلِكَ عَنْهُ سَمْعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in like manner, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAEFA","text_ar":"سَمَاعًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I received that from him by being made to hear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which virtually means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by hearsay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hearing it from him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] making the inf. n. [in each case] to be of a different form from that of the verb to which it belongs [in respect of signification; i. e., using an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEa","text_ar":"سَمِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomaEa","text_ar":"اَسْمَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, * TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumoEapN","text_ar":"سُمْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  It also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Mgh, Msb, * K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misomaEN","text_ar":"مِسْمَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, TA,) because it is the instrument of hearing, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masomaEN","text_ar":"مَسْمَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [because it is the place thereof,] (Aboo-Jebeleh, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmiEapN","text_ar":"سَامِعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misomaEN","text_ar":"مِسْمَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ear-hole;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masomaEN","text_ar":"مَسْمَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotamaEN","text_ar":"مُسْتَمَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Er-Rághib, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as a pl., (S, K,) being originally an inf. n.; but sometimes (S) it has for its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomaAEN","text_ar":"اَسْمَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomuEN","text_ar":"اَسْمُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, O, K,) a pl. of pauc., (TA,) [as is also the former,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAmiEu","text_ar":"اَسَامِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. pl., (S, Mgh, O, K,) i. e. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomaAEN","text_ar":"اَسْمَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomuEN","text_ar":"اَسْمُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, O:) [for an ex. of the pl. pl., see 2:] the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misomaEN","text_ar":"مِسْمَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAmiEu","text_ar":"مَسَامِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) or this may be an irreg. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAbihu","text_ar":"مَشَابِهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abahN","text_ar":"شَبَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sgh, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEuka A_ilaY~a","text_ar":"سَمْعُكَ اـِلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. [Incline"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thine ear to me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hear thou from me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taraqa AlkalaAmu Als~amoEu","text_ar":"طَرَقَ الكَلَامُ السَّمْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The speech struck the ear"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a pl. in the Kur [ii. 6], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xatama","text_ar":"خَتَمَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu EalaY quluwbihimo waEalaY samiEohimo","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ عَلَى قُلُوبِهِمْ وَعَلَى سَمِعْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God hath set a seal upon their hearts and upon their ears"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) One also says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN EaZiymu AlmisomaEayoni","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ عَظِيمُ المِسْمَعَيْنِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is great in the ears."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa bayona samoEi AlA^aroDi wabaSarihaA","text_ar":"هُوَ بَيْنَ سَمْعِ الاَرْضِ وَبَصَرِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is not known whither he has repaired:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is between the ears of the people of the land and their eyes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so that they neither hear him nor see him,] the prefixed noun"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ahol","text_ar":"اَهْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"being suppressed: (AO, K, * TA:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a void land, wherein is no one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, K;) i. e., none hears his speech, nor does any see him, except [the wild animals of] the desert land: (K:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the length and breadth of the land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloqaY nafosahu bayona samoEi AlA^aroDi wabaSarihaA","text_ar":"اَلْقَى نَفْسَهُ بَيْنَ سَمْعِ الاَرْضِ وَبَصَرِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exposed himself to perdition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imperilled himself, and cast himself no one knew where:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Th:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cast himself where no voice of man was heard, nor eye of man seen."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) ―         -b5-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What rests in the ear, of a thing which one hears."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoEN","text_ar":"سِمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places, beside the two places before referred to."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","Mgh","O","AZ","IAar","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n20716","headword_ar":"سِمْعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", either as an inf. n. or as a a simple subst. (Lh, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a simoEFA laA","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ سِمْعًا لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bilogFA","text_ar":"بِلْغًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA balogFA","text_ar":"لَا بَلْغًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEFA","text_ar":"سَمْعًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoEN laA","text_ar":"سِمْعٌ لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bilogN","text_ar":"بِلْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA balogN","text_ar":"لَا بَلْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) a form of prayer, (K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God, may it be heard of but not fulfilled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may it be heard but not come to:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may it be heard but not need to be come to:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it is said by him who hears tidings not pleasing to him: (K:) Ks says that it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I hear of calamities but may they not come to me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoEu A^u*uniY fulaAnFA yaquwlu","text_ar":"سِمْعُ اُذُنِى فُلَانًا يَقُولُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isomaAEN","text_ar":"اـِسْمَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAluwA *`lika simoEa A^u*uniY","text_ar":"قَالُوا ذٰلِكَ سِمْعَ اُذُنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~amahu simoEahumo","text_ar":"كَلَّمَهُ سِمْعَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) both explained above: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mention, fame, report, that is heard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAEN","text_ar":"سَمَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fame,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good report;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAEN","text_ar":"سَمَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba simoEuhu","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ سِمْعُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"فِى النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His fame,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good report, went among mankind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And the Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA wasamoEi","text_ar":"لَا وَسَمْعِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasimoEi All~`h","text_ar":"وَسِمْعِ اللّٰه"},{"kind":"text","text":",] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA wa *ikori A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"لَا وَ ذِكْرِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"No, by the glory of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  [It is also used as an"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1429},{"kind":"text","text":"epithet: thus,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN simoEN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ سِمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yusam~iEu","text_ar":"يُسَمِّعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who makes"},{"kind":"text","text":"others"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to hear"},{"kind":"text","text":"of him]: or one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A@moruw^N *uw simoEK","text_ar":"هٰذَا ا@مْرُوٌ ذُو سِمْعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uwsamaAEK","text_ar":"ذُوسَمَاعٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a man of fame,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"notoriety"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K,) whether"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain mongrel beast of prey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offspring of the wolf, begotten from the hyena:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": they assert that it does not die a natural death, like the serpent, (K, TA,) but by some accident that befalls it, not knowing diseases and maladies; and that it is unequalled by any other animal in running, (TA,) its running being quicker than [the flight of] the bird; and its leap exceeding thirty cubits, (K, TA,) or twenty. (TA.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Als~imoEi AlA^azal~i","text_ar":"مِنَ السِّمْعِ الاَزَلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomaEu","text_ar":"اَسْمَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More quick of hearing than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smE","text_ar":"سمع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is lean in the buttocks and thighs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than the light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smE","text_ar":"سمع"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and sometimes they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomaEu mino simoEK","text_ar":"اَسْمَعُ مِنْ سِمْعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more quick of hearing than a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smE","text_ar":"سمع"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Mgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n20730","headword_ar":"سُمَّعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Light, active,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agile:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and applied as an epithet to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guwl","text_ar":"غُول"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}